## Hard Stop UI Pattern

The Community Voice Hard Stop is enforced at the server. But the UI must prepare the org for it honestly, not surprise them with a wall.

```jsx
// Show this BEFORE the org begins community engagement — not after
export function HardStopPrepNotice() {
  return (
    <div className="bg-rw-green text-white rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
      <h3 className="font-georgia text-xl font-bold mb-2">
        Rootwork will wait for you here.
      </h3>
      <p className="text-white/90 leading-relaxed">
        The next step is real engagement — interviews, listening sessions, or meetings with community members. Rootwork will not unlock the next stage until you return and document who was in the room, who wasn't, and why.
      </p>
      <p className="text-white/70 text-sm mt-3">
        This is not a checkbox. It's the work.
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

