## API Call Pattern from Frontend

Frontend components never call Claude directly. They call the backend.

```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT — call your own backend
async function generateMissionDraft() {
  setLoading(true);
  const res = await fetch('/api/stage01/mission-draft', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Authorization': `Bearer ${session.access_token}` },
    body: JSON.stringify({ orgId })
  });
  const { draft, flags } = await res.json();
  setMissionDraft(draft);
  setMissionFlags(flags);
  setLoading(false);
}

// ❌ WRONG — never call Anthropic from the frontend
const anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: '...' });
```

---

## Accessibility Rules

- All form inputs have associated `<label>` elements
- All interactive elements are keyboard navigable
- Color is never the only indicator of state — always pair with text or icon
- Font sizes never below 14px for body content
- Stage progress indicators include text labels, not just icons or colors

---

## What This Agent Does Not Do

- Does not generate Supabase queries (use schema-agent rules)
- Does not write Claude agent prompts (use api-agent rules)
- Does not write Express routes (use api-agent rules)
